message.content:
 To align a row of divs to the right using flex in CSS, follow these steps:

1. Add the `display` property with value `flex` to the container element (parent div) of the divs you want to align. This will make the container act as a flex container.

2. Set the `justify-content` property of the container to `flex-end`. This will align the items in the row to the right side of the container.

Here's an example using HTML and CSS:

HTML:
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="box"></div>
  <div class="box"></div>
  <div class="box"></div>
</div>
```

CSS:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.box {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  margin: 10px;
  background-color: lightblue;
}
```
This will result in the following output:
<div class="container">
  <div class="box"></div>
  <div class="box"></div>
  <div class="box"></div>
</div>

In this example, the three divs with the class "box" are aligned to the right side of their parent container.
